m or hanging on to them. Any sadhaka who can gain a siddhi, can also let=\r\n go of that siddhi whenever he/she wants. &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; Speaking of Karma, ev=\r\nerything has a karma of it&#39;s own. Tantra, as it stands today, is roughly di=\r\nvided into two major geographic and philosophical demarcations. The style p=\r\nracticed\n in South India - mostly Dakshina Margi - and that practiced in Be=\r\nngal and adjacent areas - mostly Vama Margi. In my personal opinion, the ad=\r\nherents of the path in both cases, generally speaking, have been trapped in=\r\n two delusions born out of collateral byproducts of their respective paths.=\r\n The first step of Shakti sadhana is generating shakti. Second step is hold=\r\ning the shakti. Third step is channeling the shakti. In view of this, one s=\r\nchool of Tantra that is prevalent today has tied itself up in too much of t=\r\nechnicalities, such that on an average they forget to capture shakti (here =\r\nshakti means energy, not Shakti the supreme Goddess). WHile the other schoo=\r\nl is able to generate and hold shakti much better, only to commercialize th=\r\ne same and/or misuse it (generally speaking, &gt; &gt;=C2=A0 expcetions are there=\r\n too). End result, both eventually do not end up producing enough genuine T=\r\nantrik saints. &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;&lt; &gt; &gt; i am wondering &quot;if at all&quot; and &quot;what kind&quot; of=\r\n\n karmic liabilities one might be getting into ?&gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; A fair exchange =\r\nis never a robbery, as Vimalananda says. Theoretically, when the *right per=\r\nson* performs many of the things mentioned in that blog, (and some of the s=\r\ntuff there is not exactly accurately portrayed), he/she will know how to ba=\r\nlance the karmic impact well. In the hands of an immature individual, it ca=\r\nn lead to disaster. Further, the so called division between &#39;classical Tant=\r\nra&#39; and &#39;folk Tantra&#39; is not as sharp and clear as it i